# Component Authoring Rules

## Design Tokens — Never Hardcode Values

- Use semantic Tailwind classes: `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `border`, `rounded-lg`
- Never use Tailwind's color palette: `bg-blue-500`, `text-gray-900`
- Never use inline styles with color values: `style={{ color: '#000' }}`
- Never use `@apply` — use utility classes directly in JSX
- Use token pairs for contrast: `bg-primary` + `text-primary-foreground`

## Component Structure

- Use `'use client'` for any component with hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs
- Export components as `export default function ComponentName(): ReactElement`
- Use `useId()` for form label associations, never hardcoded IDs
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Include `data-slot` attribute on wrapper elements for testability
- Include the Apache 2.0 copyright header

## ShadCN UI

- Import from `@/components/ui/<component>`
- Use `React.ComponentProps<>` for typing, not custom interfaces
- Use CVA (`class-variance-authority`) for component variants
- Use `Slot` from `@radix-ui/react-slot` for polymorphic `asChild` pattern

## File Naming

- Kebab-case directories: `my-component/`
- `index.tsx` for main component files
- Stories in `stories/index.stories.tsx` subdirectory

## Storybook

- Import from `'@storybook/react-vite'` (not `'@storybook/react'`)
- Import test utils from `'storybook/test'` (not `'@storybook/testing-library'`)
- Import actions from `'storybook/actions'` (not `'@storybook/addon-actions'`)
- Use `waitForStorybookReady(canvasElement)` before assertions in play functions
- Use `globals: { viewport: 'mobile2' }` for mobile stories
- Include `tags: ['autodocs', 'interaction']`

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

- Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation — never `<div onClick>`
- Every `<input>` must have an associated `<label>` with matching `htmlFor`/`id`
- Use `aria-label`, `aria-describedby`, `aria-expanded` where appropriate
- Focus styles: `focus-visible:border-ring focus-visible:ring-ring/50 focus-visible:ring-[3px]`
- All interactive elements must be keyboard navigable (Tab, Enter, Space)

## Internationalization

- Use `useTranslation('extensionName')` for all user-facing strings
- Translation files go in `extensions/<name>/locales/en-GB.json`
- Never hardcode user-visible text in JSX

## TypeScript

- No `any` type — explicitly type all props and data
- Use strict mode
- Use `ReactElement` as return type annotation

## What Does Not Exist

- No `tailwind.config.ts` — Tailwind v4 uses `@theme inline` in `app.css`
- No `PluginProviders` — providers are injected via Storybook global decorator
- No `target-config.json.snippet` — the file is `target-config.json`
